article.description: — Isaiah Addo-Ankrah had 18 points in Denver's 67-65 victory over Idaho on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Addo-Ankrah scores 18, Denver beats Idaho 67-65
article.story: MOSCOW, Idaho -- — Isaiah Addo-Ankrah had 18 points in Denver's 67-65 victory over Idaho on Wednesday night. Addo-Ankrah added seven rebounds for the Pioneers (5-3). Touko Tainamo scored 16 points while going 6 of 19 from the floor, including 0 for 5 from 3-point range, and 4 for 6 from the line, and added six rebounds. Tommy Bruner had 14 points and was 4 of 16 shooting, including 2 for 6 from 3-point range, and went 4 for 4 from the line. D'Angelo Minnis led the Vandals (3-4) in scoring, finishing with 15 points and seven assists. Idaho also got 14 points, two steals and two blocks from Trevon Blassingame. Julius Mims also recorded 10 points, 10 rebounds and three blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
